description:
Redesign PaneListLive to use the Graphite design system. Replace all inline styles with CSS classes, improve visual hierarchy of session rows, and polish project grouping, filters, and sync indicators.

**Output files:**
- lib/spotter_web/live/pane_list_live.ex - rewrite render/1 and component functions, replace all inline styles
- priv/static/assets/spotter.css - add .page-header, .filter-bar, .filter-btn, .project-section, .subagent-toggle, .sync-*, .section-heading classes

**Technical specs:**
- .page-header: display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
- .page-header-actions: display: flex; gap: var(--space-2);
- .filter-bar: display: flex; gap: var(--space-2); flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
- .filter-btn: padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); background: var(--surface-2); color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: var(--text-xs);
- .filter-btn.is-active: background: #1a3d2c; color: var(--accent-green); border-color: #2a6a4a;
- .project-section: margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
- .project-name: font-size: var(--text-lg); font-weight: 600;
- .project-count: color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: var(--text-sm);
- Session table: use base table styles, .btn-success for Review, .btn for Hide, .btn-ghost for toggles
- .subagent-toggle: color: var(--accent-purple); font-size: var(--text-xs); cursor: pointer;
- Sync indicators: .sync-syncing (amber + pulse animation), .sync-completed (green), .sync-error (red)
- .section-heading: font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
- Utility classes: .text-muted { color: var(--text-tertiary); }, .text-xs { font-size: var(--text-xs); }, .text-error { color: var(--accent-red); }
- Remove "Debug Terminal" link from header
- Use class={"filter-btn #{if condition, do: "is-active"}"} instead of inline style interpolation

**Source references:**
- lib/spotter_web/live/pane_list_live.ex - full render function (300+ lines with inline styles)
- lib/spotter/transcripts/session_presenter.ex - label helper functions

**Edge cases:**
- Preserve all phx-click, phx-value-*, phx-disable-with attributes exactly
- Keep AshComputer computer macro blocks unchanged
- pane_table component uses @badge assign - update to new badge classes

**Architecture constraints:**
- Do not change assign logic, mount, handle_event, or handle_info. Only modify render/1 and private component functions.

**Definition of done:**
- Zero inline style= attributes in pane_list_live.ex render
- All colors reference CSS custom properties, not hex literals
- Filter buttons use .filter-btn / .filter-btn.is-active
- All buttons use .btn variants
- Debug Terminal link removed
- Visual hierarchy clear: page title > project sections > session rows

Redesign SessionLive with a unified dark theme across all three panels. Replace the light transcript theme with dark, add tabbed sidebar (Commits | Annotations | Errors), and apply semantic left-border accents to transcript rows.

**Output files:**
- lib/spotter_web/live/session_live.ex - rewrite render/1, replace inline styles, add active_sidebar_tab assign + switch_sidebar_tab event
- priv/static/assets/spotter.css - replace transcript tokens, add .session-layout, .session-terminal, .session-transcript, .session-sidebar, .sidebar-tabs, .sidebar-tab, .commit-card, .annotation-card, .annotation-form, .terminal-connecting classes. Update all .transcript-row variants to dark theme.
- assets/js/app.js - update xterm.js theme to Graphite palette, update TranscriptSelection highlight colors

**Technical specs:**

Three-panel layout CSS:
- .session-layout: display: flex; gap: 0; height: 100vh;
- .session-terminal: flex: 2; overflow-x: auto; padding: var(--space-4);
- .session-transcript: flex: 1; padding: var(--space-4); overflow-y: auto; border-left: 1px solid var(--border-default); background: var(--surface-1);
- .session-sidebar: flex: 1; background: var(--surface-1); padding: var(--space-4); overflow-y: auto; border-left: 1px solid var(--border-default);

Transcript rows (dark theme):
- .transcript-row: padding: 2px var(--space-2); border-left: 2px solid transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); line-height: 1.5;
- .transcript-row.is-active: background: rgba(91,156,245,0.1); border-left-color: var(--accent-blue);
- .transcript-row.is-user .row-text: color: var(--accent-blue);
- .transcript-row.is-thinking: background: var(--surface-2); font-style: italic; .row-text color: var(--text-secondary);
- .transcript-row.is-tool-use: background: var(--surface-2); border-left-color: var(--accent-cyan); font-weight: 500;
- .transcript-row.is-tool-result: border-left-color: var(--border-default); padding-left: 14px; .row-text color: var(--text-secondary);
- .transcript-row.is-subagent: border-left-color: var(--accent-purple); background: rgba(167,139,250,0.05);
- .subagent-badge: background: var(--accent-purple); color: var(--surface-0); font-size: var(--text-xs); padding: 0 var(--space-1); border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer;

Error panel (dark):
- .transcript-error-panel: background: rgba(232,84,84,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(232,84,84,0.2); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-3);
- .transcript-error-item: clickable, hover: rgba(232,84,84,0.1) bg;

Tabbed sidebar:
- New assign: active_sidebar_tab (default :commits) in mount
- New handle_event("switch_sidebar_tab", %{"tab" => tab}, socket)
- .sidebar-tabs: flex row, border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-default);
- .sidebar-tab: padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--text-tertiary); border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
- .sidebar-tab.is-active: color: var(--accent-blue); border-bottom-color: var(--accent-blue);
- Tab buttons with counts: Commits (N), Annotations (N), Errors (N)

Commit cards: .commit-card (surface-2 bg, radius-md), .commit-hash (amber, mono, text-xs), .commit-subject (text-primary, text-xs), .commit-branch (tertiary, text-xs)

Annotation cards: .annotation-card (surface-2, hover: surface-3, cursor: pointer), .annotation-text (mono, text-xs, max-height: 60px, overflow-y: auto), .annotation-comment (text-primary, text-sm), .annotation-meta (flex between, margin-top), .annotation-time (text-xs, tertiary)

Annotation form: .annotation-form (surface-2, radius-md, padding), .annotation-form-hint, .annotation-form-preview (mono, max-height: 100px), .annotation-form-actions (flex, gap)

Terminal connecting state: .terminal-connecting (centered, tertiary text)

xterm.js theme update (assets/js/app.js lines 48-53):
  theme: { background: "#0c0e14", foreground: "#e8eaf0", cursor: "#5b9cf5", selectionBackground: "rgba(91, 156, 245, 0.3)" }

TranscriptSelection highlight colors (app.js lines 308-309):
  background: "rgba(91, 156, 245, 0.15)", borderLeft: "2px solid var(--accent-amber)"

Convert anchor_color/1 to Graphite accents: tool_use -> accent-amber, user -> accent-blue, result -> accent-green, text -> accent-purple

**Source references:**
- lib/spotter_web/live/session_live.ex - render function (lines 478-676)
- priv/static/assets/spotter.css - current light transcript styles
- assets/js/app.js - Terminal hook theme (lines 44-54), TranscriptSelection highlight (lines 307-319)

**Edge cases:**
- phx-update="replace" re-renders entire transcript - CSS classes survive
- Keep debug anchor inline styles (dynamic anchor_color/1), convert to Graphite accents
- Tab switching is the ONE new Elixir logic addition

**Architecture constraints:**
- Minimize Elixir logic changes. Only new assigns/events for tab switching.
- Do not change transcript rendering logic in TranscriptRenderer.
- xterm.js theme set via JS, not CSS.

**Definition of done:**
- All three panels use dark backgrounds from Graphite palette
- No light-theme colors (#f8fafc, #ffffff, #f1f5f9) remain in spotter.css
- Transcript rows use semantic left-border accents: blue for user, cyan for tool_use, purple for subagent
- Right sidebar has working Commits/Annotations/Errors tabs
- Terminal background matches surface-0 (#0c0e14)
- Zero inline style= in session_live.ex render (except dynamic debug anchor dots)

Replace the per-scroll server roundtrip in the Terminal JS hook with local binary search over the breakpoint map. When scrolling, client looks up current terminal line in precomputed map and scrolls transcript panel — zero network calls.

**Output files:**
- assets/js/app.js (modify)

**Technical specs:**

1. Add to mounted() after `this._term = term`:
   this._breakpointMap = null
   this._debugAnchors = null
   this._lastSyncedId = null
   this._showDebug = false

2. In _connectChannel, add handler:
   this.handleEvent("breakpoint_map", ({ entries }) => {
     this._breakpointMap = entries
   })

3. Replace term.onScroll block (lines 98-110):
   let scrollTimeout = null
   term.onScroll(() => {
     clearTimeout(scrollTimeout)
     scrollTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
       const topLine = term.buffer.active.viewportY
       if (this._breakpointMap && this._breakpointMap.length > 0) {
         const messageId = this._lookupMessage(topLine)
         if (messageId && messageId !== this._lastSyncedId) {
           this._lastSyncedId = messageId
           const el = document.querySelector(`[data-message-id="${messageId}"]`)
           if (el) el.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "center" })
         }
       } else {
         // Legacy fallback
         const buffer = term.buffer.active
         const lines = []
         for (let i = buffer.viewportY; i < buffer.viewportY + term.rows; i++) {
           const line = buffer.getLine(i)
           if (line) lines.push(line.translateToString(true))
         }
         this.pushEvent("terminal_scrolled", { visible_text: lines.join("\n") })
       }
     }, 150)
   })

4. Binary search function:
   _lookupMessage(terminalLine) {
     const map = this._breakpointMap
     if (!map || map.length === 0) return null
     let lo = 0, hi = map.length - 1, result = map[0].id
     while (lo <= hi) {
       const mid = (lo + hi) >>> 1
       if (map[mid].t <= terminalLine) { result = map[mid].id; lo = mid + 1 }
       else { hi = mid - 1 }
     }
     return result
   }

5. Keep handleEvent("scroll_to_message") for legacy/error-jump path.

**Source references:**
- assets/js/app.js — mounted (line 10), _connectChannel (line 44), onScroll (lines 98-110), handleEvent scroll_to_message (line 113)
- Breakpoint map format: [{t: integer, id: string}, ...] sorted ascending by t

**Edge cases:**
- breakpointMap null/empty → legacy pushEvent fallback
- viewportY = 0 → returns first entry's id (correct)
- Scroll past last breakpoint → returns last entry's id (correct)
- _lastSyncedId prevents redundant scrollIntoView
- Debounce reduced from 300ms to 150ms (local lookup is instant)

**Definition of Done:**
- All requirements implemented
- esbuild compiles without errors
- Manual: scroll terminal → transcript follows with no network activity
- Manual: no pane → legacy sync still works
- Manual: rapid scroll → no jank
